{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We also learned other disciplines over there, in addition to-- in addition to-- like I was in the carpenters' shop, cabinetmaker shop, they also had shoemakers, for instance.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We also learned how to knit and to darn socks, because a lot of things were done by ourselves.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, I'd darn old socks after a while.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was able to knit-- I knit a sweater for myself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Most of the other kids did the same thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I don't recall how, as far as clothes are concerned, how we kept getting clothes, because as I get older, I must have had bigger clothes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I know there must have been hand me downs and so forth, but I just don't remember the details of that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a fairly amount of normalcy there, right.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, there were other things that happened, like, for instance, one of my--my father's brother, and his wife and my cousin Otto left Austria, and fled to-- they went to Italy at the time.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I got a card from them saying, they're leaving-- they're leaving Italy, they're going to go to Chile.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was hoping I was able to go with them, but there just was no way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I still have the correspondence from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the way, that's the only thing I still have.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I kept correspondence, and I kept the pictures.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I have most of those things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had the cards from other people, distant relatives who were leaving, who would give me the straight scoop about-- about-- for instance, my-- this couple, the cousins who had come to live at our home after-- after they'd been kicked out.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was sent to the Dachau-- both of them were sent to Dachau at the time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I know that others had left Austria.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
